I need to identify the financing costs incurred by the enterprise based on the income statement.

In a typical income statement, financing costs usually appear as "Financial Expenses" or similar terms. These expenses represent the costs associated with borrowing money or raising capital for business operations.

Looking at the income statement provided in the problem:

The line item labeled "Financial Expenses" shows an amount of 297417.97 on 2024-02-05.

This represents the financing costs incurred by the enterprise to raise funds needed for production and operation.
